{{Orphan|date=September 2018}}
[[File:Johan_Christian_Dahl_-_Stugunøset_at_Filefjell_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg|thumb|300px]] '''''The Stugunøset in the Filefjeld''''' (Norwegian - ''Stugunøset på Filefjeld'', ''Stugunøset på Fillefjell'' or ''Stugunøset på Filefjell'') is an 1851 painting by [[JC Dahl]], now in the [[National Gallery of Norway]]. It shows the Støgonøse mountain in the [[Filefjell]] area in the [[Valdres]] district and was painted just after the artist's last trip to Valdres in 1850, aged 62. He based it on a sketch he had made on the high mountain ridge north of Utrøvatnet.
In 1852 it was sold to the [[Oslo Kunstforening|Christiania Art Society]], which sold it the following year to [[Wilhelm Adelsten Maribo]], who left it to its current owner in 1901.
==Sources== *http://urn.nb.no/URN:NBN:no-nb_digibok_2007111501066&struct=DIV132 *http://www.google.com/culturalinstitute/asset-viewer/stugun%C3%B8set-at-filefjell/IwH09jau3mEorg?projectId=art-project
